[h1]Where to Find Horses[/h1]
They can be found in some farms, ranches, and stables around the map. You can find 4 different breeds each with 2 color variants:
[list]
[*] American Quarter (Palomino, Blue Roan)
[*] American Paint (Tobiano, Overo)
[*] Appaloosa (Grulla Blanket, Leopard)
[*] Thoroughbred (Bay, Flea-Bitten Grey)
[/list]

[h1]Keybinds[/h1]
[i]*Check the Mod Options to change the keybind![/i]
[list]
[*] [b]Mount / Dismount[/b] (default: interact key): Get on or off your horse, and cancel it with the same key if needed.
[*] [b]Walk[/b] (default: player movement keys).
[*] [b]Trot toggle[/b] (default: X).
[*] [b]Gallop[/b] (default: Left Shift).*
[*] [b]Jump[/b] (default: Space) - Jump over small fences, [b]requires the horse to gallop[/b].*
[*] [b]Kick[/b] zombies (default: Space) - Kick zombies on the side of the horse with your foot, same key as your pushing key but no need to aim.
[/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PZ-HorseTeam/HorseMod/refs/heads/main/Steam/description/stances.gif[/img]

[h1]Gear and Equipment[/h1]
When you have equipment in your inventory, you can equip them on the horse from the horse context menu from a menu named "Gear". Currently the equipments available for the horse are:
[list]
[*] Saddle - not required to ride a horse, but without it your character will get pain in the groin.
[*] Reins
[*] Saddlebags - allows you to store items on your horse and ride around with them.
[/list]

